summary: This is an FBI FD-1087 evidence inventory form listing items seized, including taped conversations, audio tapes, photo line-ups, and various papers related to a Palm Beach Police Department investigation. The evidence was collected on August 28, 2006, and was held by the Miami FBI office, with a final inventory noted on July 20, 2021.

keyFacts: The document is an FBI evidence inventory (FD-1087) for items related to Palm Beach Police Department case numbers (e.g., PBPD 05-237).
The seized evidence includes multiple audio tapes, a taped conversation, a photo line-up, and various papers containing flight information, phone numbers, and initials (e.g., N.M., J.B., C.W., G.).
The evidence was originally collected on August 28, 2006, and was held by the Miami FBI office, with a final inventory conducted on July 20, 2021.
